      "lastChapterApiLink": "/api/BSB/EXO/40.json",
      "name": "Exodus",
      "numberOfChapters": 40,
      "order": 2,
      "sha256": "f036511ae774f868007d0f0b59ff020699f21228d9293b390f4fc9d3f6f2dee2",
      "title": "Exodus",
      "totalNumberOfVerses": 1213,
      "translationId": "BSB"
    },
    "chapter": {
      "content": [
        {
          "content": [
            "The Israelites Multiply in Egypt"
          ],
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "These are the names of the sons of Israel who went to Egypt with Jacob, each with his family:"
          ],
          "number": 1,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "type": "line_break"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "Reuben, Simeon, Levi, and Judah;"
          ],
          "number": 2,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "type": "line_break"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "Issachar, Zebulun, and Benjamin;"
          ],
          "number": 3,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "type": "line_break"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "Dan and Naphtali;",
            {
              "lineBreak": true
            },
            "Gad and Asher."
          ],
          "number": 4,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "type": "line_break"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "The descendants of Jacob numbered seventy",
            {
              "noteId": 1595
            },
            "in all, including Joseph, who was already in Egypt."
          ],
          "number": 5,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "type": "line_break"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "Now Joseph and all his brothers and all that generation died,"
          ],
          "number": 6,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "but the Israelites were fruitful and increased rapidly; they multiplied and became exceedingly numerous, so that the land was filled with them."
          ],
          "number": 7,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "Oppression by a New King"
          ],
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "line_break"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "Then a new king, who did not know Joseph, came to power in Egypt."
          ],
          "number": 8,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "“Look,” he said to his people, “the Israelites have become too numerous and too powerful for us."
          ],
          "number": 9,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "Come, let us deal shrewdly with them, or they will increase even more; and if a war breaks out, they may join our enemies, fight against us, and leave the country.",
            {
              "noteId": 1596
            },
            "”"
          ],
          "number": 10,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "type": "line_break"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "So the Egyptians appointed taskmasters over the Israelites to oppress them with forced labor. As a result, they built Pithom and Rameses as store cities for Pharaoh."
          ],
          "number": 11,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "But the more they were oppressed, the more they multiplied and flourished; so the Egyptians came to dread the Israelites."
          ],
          "number": 12,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "type": "line_break"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "They worked the Israelites ruthlessly"
          ],
          "number": 13,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "and made their lives bitter with hard labor in brick and mortar, and with all kinds of work in the fields. Every service they imposed was harsh."
          ],
          "number": 14,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "type": "line_break"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "Then the king of Egypt said to the Hebrew midwives, whose names were Shiphrah and Puah,"
          ],
          "number": 15,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "“When you help the Hebrew women give birth, observe them on the birthstools. If the child is a son, kill him; but if it is a daughter, let her live.”"
          ],
          "number": 16,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "type": "line_break"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "The midwives, however, feared God and did not do as the king of Egypt had instructed; they let the boys live."
          ],
          "number": 17,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "So the king of Egypt summoned the midwives and asked them, “Why have you done this? Why have you let the boys live?”"
          ],
          "number": 18,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "type": "line_break"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "The midwives answered Pharaoh, “The Hebrew women are not like the Egyptian women, for they are vigorous and give birth before a midwife arrives.”"
          ],
          "number": 19,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "type": "line_break"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "So God was good to the midwives, and the people multiplied and became even more numerous."
          ],
          "number": 20,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "And because the midwives feared God, He gave them families of their own."
          ],
          "number": 21,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "type": "line_break"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "Then Pharaoh commanded all his people: “Every son born to the Hebrews",
            {
              "noteId": 1597
            },
            "you must throw into the Nile, but every daughter you may allow to live.”"
          ],
          "number": 22,
          "type": "verse"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        {
          "caller": "+",
          "noteId": 1595,
          "reference": {
            "chapter": 1,
            "verse": 5
          },
          "text": "MT (see also Genesis 46:27); DSS and LXX (see also Acts 7:14) seventy-five"
        },
        {
          "caller": "+",
          "noteId": 1596,
          "reference": {
            "chapter": 1,
            "verse": 10
          },
          "text": "Or and take the country"
        },
        {
          "caller": "+",
          "noteId": 1597,
          "reference": {
            "chapter": 1,
            "verse": 22
          },
          "text": "SP, LXX, and Targum Yonaton; Hebrew does not include to the Hebrews."
        }
      ],
      "number": 1
    },
